description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crewkerne Health Centre &lt;/strong&gt;have an exciting opportunity for highly motivated and flexible individual to join the practice as a Reception /Administration Supervisor on a permanent basis. The post available will be working &lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working pattern to be discussed at interview.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rate of pay will be £10.40 - £11.40 per hour, depending on experience with the benefit of a NEST pension.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be responsible for the leadership of all operational functions delivered by the Reception/Administration Team and for overseeing the smooth and effective running of the Patient Services within the Practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with the Medical and Nursing leads within the practice to ensure the safe and effective staffing of the practice and to build, develop, support and motivate the Reception/Administration team within the practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may also be required to provide additional cover for holidays and sickness, therefore flexibility is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have excellent communication skills and have the ability to Lead and work as part of a team. You will be IT literate and be able to work accurately and prioritise your workload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous management or supervisory experience is essential and previous experience of working in a medical environment is desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please open the attached Job description for a comprehensive overview of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information contact Ruth Bagg, Practice Manager via email ruth.bagg@nhs.net or phone 01460 72435&lt;/p&gt;
